create a branch -> git branch branchName
move to branch -> git checkout branchName

create and move to branch -> git checkout -b branchName

git stash -> temporarily save the changes and clear your modified files from new changes and store it for later use.
git stash pop -> apply the saved changes and clean your stash(delete all from stash)
git stash apply apply the saved changes, keeping the modified files still in stash
git stash clear -> delete all changes in stash.
stash acts like a stack ->LIFO